Enum CallState

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Enum<CallState>
      jibe.sdk.client.call.CallState
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CallState>
public enum CallState
extends java.lang.Enum<CallState>

Enumeration for the different call states, plus utility methods for converting between call-state value and call-state type.

Enum Constant Summary
ADDING_VIDEO
          An update of the call is being signaled to the remote party, adding video (originating and terminating side).
ESTABLISHED
          The call was established, and media is now flowing between the call parties (originating and terminating side).
ESTABLISHING
          The call was accepted, and media setup is now taking place (originating and terminating side).
INCOMING
          The call request was received, but has not yet been answered (only valid on terminating side).
OUTGOING
          The remote party is being alerted about the incoming call (only valid on originating side).
REMOVING_VIDEO
          An update of the call is being signaled to the remote party, removing video (originating and terminating side).
TERMINATED
          The call has been terminated (originating and terminating side).
TERMINATING
          The termination of the call is being signaled to the remote party, or a request for termination has been received (originating and terminating side).
TRANSFERRING
          The call is being transfered to a third party (only valid on originating side).
UNKNOWN
          The state is unknown - the default value when the session is created.
